As the title says, through the API today parsing the "mainbranch" attribute using the PUT method does absolutely nothing, the API gives a 200 code and does not alter the attribute within the repository\\
The expected behavior in this case is for the attribute "mainbranch" to be updated parsing it through a json, like this:

{code}
#!bash


curl PUT -u <userAuthString> -H "Content-Type: application/json" https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/<repo_slug>-d &#x27;{"mainbranch": { "type":"branch", "name": "<newmainbranch>"}}&#x27;

{code}

I get the following error when trying to copy files from a previous build stage

{code}
#!generic

Step 7/18 : COPY --from=uikit /app/binders-ui-kit.tgz  /app

failed to copy files: failed to copy file: Container ID 166536 cannot be mapped to a host ID
{code}

The file in question and its parent directoyr are owned by a user {{node (id:1000)}} (inside the uikit container). This is also the same user of the build container by using the {{USER}} directive.

Please see the attached screenshot. There is no space between files, from the second file onwards. This is due to the following code:

h3. issue-attachment-list.less
{code}
.issue-attachment-list li {
  position: relative;
  float: left;
  margin: 0 15px 13px 0;
}
{code}

h3. reset.less
{code}
body.adg3 dd+dd, body.adg3 li+li {
  margin: 0;
}
{code}

Simply adding {{!important}} to CSS code in {{issue-attachment-list.less}} fixes the problem.

Hello!

I very like pipelines and I want to thank the team for that useful service.

I have a suggestion to use ENV variables for {{definitions}} section.\\
I&#x27;m developing laravel project and I think that using ENV vars for services credentials would be very convenient.

{code}
#!yml

definitions:
  services:
    mysql:
      image: mysql:8
      environment:
        MYSQL_DATABASE: ${DB_DATABASE}
        MYSQL_USER: ${DB_USERNAME}
        MYSQL_PASSWORD: ${DB_PASSWORD}
        MYSQL_RANDOM_ROOT_PASSWORD: yes
{code}

I know that for test env it is not critical, but I think that specifying services credentials in one place would be more convenient.

Thanks!
